verbose_text: Arresten is a 26-kDa protein fragment previously shown to inhibit proliferation and migration of endothelial cells and to inhibit hypoxia induced increase in expression and vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF) and hypoxia inducible factor 1a (HIF-1alpha).
evidence: inhibit proliferation and migration of endothelial cells and to inhibit hypoxia-induced increase in expression and vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF) and hypoxia-inducible factor
